### Step 1: Rewrite in a Convenient Form

Express the factor as a sum or difference that uses a multiple of 10, 100, or a whole number.

[
7 \cdot 497 = 7(500 - 3) = 7 \cdot 500 - 7 \cdot 3
]

[
6(525) = 6(500 + 25) = 6 \cdot 500 + 6 \cdot 25
]

[
36 \cdot 3\frac{1}{4} = 36\left(3 + \frac{1}{4}\right) = 36 \cdot 3 + 36 \cdot \frac{1}{4}
]

[
5 \cdot 89 = 5(90 - 1) = 5 \cdot 90 - 5 \cdot 1
]

[
9 \cdot 99 = 9(100 - 1) = 9 \cdot 100 - 9 \cdot 1
